The teachers service commission is set to roll out a countrywide biometric registration of all teachers under its employment. Ahead of this important exercise the commission is holding a stakeholder meeting at KICD with a view to collecting before a pilot project over the same is initiated. The biometric registration of teachers shall entail validation of data of teachers under employment of TSC in all public primary and secondary schools. Knut secretary general Wilson Sossion has welcomed the move saying it will help the government in planning.